In remarks made on March 3, 2020, President Trump addressed several topics including the coronavirus, funding from Congress, the Olympics in Japan, the Fed's funds rate, his conversation with the leader of the Taliban, the Democratic establishment's treatment of Bernie Sanders, healthcare for patients without insurance, the upcoming election, domestic travel restrictions, downplaying the coronavirus, NCAA's decision to have no fans in the stands, travel restrictions to Italy and South Korea, and the performance of the stock market. The President expressed confidence in the government's handling of the coronavirus situation and his willingness to debate any Democratic opponent. He also criticized the Federal Reserve and expressed disappointment in their actions.